article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- — Arne Osojnik scored 22 points to help Eastern Michigan hold off Western Michigan 70-67 on Tuesday night. Osojnik added seven rebounds for the Eagles (12-16, 5-10 Mid-American Conference). Tyson Acuff had 17 points and three steals. Jalin Billingsley totaled 13 points and eight rebounds. Javaughn Hannah led the Broncos (10-18, 7-8) with 18 points. Javonte Brown added 16 points and three blocks. Seth Hubbard pitched in with 12 points, eight rebounds and five assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
